t people burning through their pensions at the age of 55 or at the age\nof 65, because they�because that's the expectation of�because they feel they\nhave no other choice, that�or that they're�they're using it to�they're\nessentially burning the furniture to stay warm. That's our concern about it. ","index":"02040","speaker":""},{"html":"����� It\ndoes have important elements in an emergency, but we are�do have reservations.\nBut I do think that we will support this bill.","index":"02041","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Thank\nyou very much, Mr. Deputy Speaker.","index":"02042","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nDeputy Speaker:</b> The question before the House is second reading of Bill 8,\nThe Pension Benefits Amendment Act. ","index":"02043","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Is it\nthe pleasure of the House to adopt the motion? ","index":"02044","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Some\nHonourable Members:</b> Agreed.","index":"02045","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Some\nHonourable Members:</b> No.","index":"02046","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nDeputy Speaker:</b> Agreed? Agreed and so ordered. I declare the motion\ncarried. ","index":"02047","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Some\nHonourable Members:</b> No. ","index":"02048","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nDeputy Speaker:</b> Sorry? Oh, I hear a no.","index":"02049","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Voice Vote</b>","index":"02050","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Deputy Speaker:</b> All those in\nfavour of the motion, please say yea.","index":"02051","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Some Honourable Members:</b> Yea.","index":"02052","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Deputy Speaker:</b> All those\nopposed to the motion, please say nay.","index":"02053","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Some Honourable Members:</b> Nay.","index":"02054","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Deputy Speaker:</b> Order. I\njust�order. ","index":"02055","speaker":""},{"html":"����� I'm not being able to hear the\nactual people who said no to the bill. So if everybody could be quiet so that\nwe can go forwa